One of the two Nay votes, A&I representative Dr. Eugene Donald, provided a written objection. By his request, it is reproduced below.

[[div class="blockquote"]]
I stand firmly opposed to this idea. Attempts to twist narrative into our favour have historically [[[*/scp-3143|proven impossible]]], [[[*/scp-5500|backfired]]], or [[[*/scp-6747|worse]]]. I do not see why we are somehow okay with trying yet again, for what is frankly a marginal benefit. I stated it in the CGM and I will state it again here: there is no reason to assume we are the protagonists of the story, and even if we are, no reason to assume the protagonist persists.

I will submit a counterproposal by CGM 07/21, and I hope, for the sake of the Site, that it will be adopted over this.
[[/div]]
 
[[/div]]

[[/div]]

------

[[span class="st" style="color: gray"]]ADDENDUM 9881.VII:[[/span]] Death Report of Dr. Constance Treplev [[footnote]]Simultaneously designated [[span class="bt"]]Incident 9881-F[[/span]].[[/footnote]]

[[div class="darkdocument"]]

[[=]]
+ DEATH OF DR CONSTANCE TREPLEV
+++ HUMAN RESOURCES, SITE-512

+++++ //Reference number: 21061A1//

[[/=]]


[[div style="text-align: right; font-size: 0.9em; font-style: italic"]]
30/06/21
Themis Fu
Manager, HR, Site-512
[[/div]]
-----
[[span class="bt"]]**Action**:[[/span]] The family of Dr. Constance Treplev (henceforth referred to as CT) was awarded Tier-4 Compensation[[footnote]]The lowest tier of compensation payable for death, per Site-512 Insurance Directives.[[/footnote]] for her death. Dr. Constance Treplev was posthumously demoted to Researcher from Senior Researcher.

[[span class="bt"]]**Justification**[[/span]]: CT died on 14 June 2021 in a work-adjacent incident.

On 13 June, CONPROC PROPOSAL 9881:05 began implementation, under the supervision of CT. In the process, standard safety protocols were in place: critically, a non-lethal muzzle attachment was attached to SCP-9881, and its firing zone was clearly cordoned off. There were no reported safety incidents. At the end of the workday, the container to house SCP-9881 had been successfully produced, and the housing site had been excavated "80% of the way".

On 14 June, at 0637H, CT was found dead at the worksite. She had been shot in the head with SCP-9881. CCTV footage revealed she had been shot by one of her subordinates, Dr. M (anonymised), who was rapidly brought in for questioning.

In Dr. M's interrogation, they revealed their decision-making in the lead-up to CT's death. They first noted that the practical idea of killing CT had arose after Dr. M witnessed the numerous safety measures put in place in the containment of SCP-9881, but the lack of proper measures to secure the anomaly.[[footnote]]Ownership of firearms is banned in Singapore; correspondingly, only certain members of Site-512 are licensed to own and freely carry firearms.[[/footnote]] Dr. M reported that they had already intended to talk to CT in the morning about the poor workplace culture in the Narrative Energy office; however, infuriated by CT's apathy, Dr. M reported a similar compulsion to shoot and kill her, which they proceeded to do.

Dr. M further expounded on CT's role in creating a uniquely hostile work environment in Narrative Energy; they accused CT of rampant and extreme misconduct, in which she often took sole credit of joint discoveries, demoted or transferred potential competitors, encouraged in-fighting and a lack of transparency, and engaged in sexual coercion against junior male employees in the office. Dr. M claimed that CT was a "narcissist" capable of pretending otherwise when necessary, who ultimately saw herself as "the main character of the story".

Dr. M expounded on CT's actions against the interests of the Foundation and Site-512. They alleged that Dr. M had engaged in directly counter-Foundation actions, with three verifiable incidents. The first incident was her awareness, aiding and abetting of Dr. Heenan's misappropriation of Foundation resources. (For further context, see Case 21031D2.) The second and third incidents are under censor by Inspectorate, as they concern ongoing investigations.

The full transcript of Dr. M's interrogation is held solely by Inspectorate. As of 23 June 2021, Inspectorate has confirmed the above claims as they pertain to CT. Inspectorate continues to investigate AE's Narrative Energy office, reference word BERBISA. Dr. M's breach of protocol is separately handled in Case 21062A1.

As Dr. M was potentially influenced by SCP-9881, CT's death is classified as work-adjacent. However, noting her prior misconduct, a posthumous demotion and maximal reduction in compensation is recommended.

[[span class="bt"]]**Outcome**:[[/span]] Action was approved on 27 June 2021. As of 28 June 2021, the demotion has been processed. As of 29 June 2021, CT's family have received the compensation, CT's corpse, and have been provided a standard explanation for CT's death. No lasting effects observed.

[[/div]]

